.TH TERMOBULATOR 7 "2026-06-28" "termobulator 1.3.0" "Termobulator Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
termobulator \- Headless terminal emulator driver and testing framework (MCP server)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B termobulator
is a headless terminal emulator driver and testing framework. It functions primarily as a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server rather than a direct user-runnable program.
.PP
For detailed instructions and documentation, refer to the
.B README.md
file located at:
.RS
.I /usr/share/doc/termobulator/README.md
.RE
.SH MCP SERVER CONFIGURATION
To rig the
.B termobulator
binary as an MCP server, you should configure it in your MCP settings file (typically
.I mcp_config.json
or similar client configuration). Add the following server configuration entry:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "termobulator": {
      "command": "/usr/libexec/termobulator/termobulator",
      "args": [
        "--mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}
.EE
.RE
.SH LIBRARIES
The project installs two libraries for integration and testing:
.TP
.B libtermobulator
The core headless terminal emulator library.
Header:
.I /usr/include/termobulator.h
.TP
.B libtermobulator-testing
The testing framework extension containing helper APIs and GMock matchers for testing terminal output and interaction.
Header:
.I /usr/include/termobulator_testing.h
.PP
Developers should read these header files for detailed API definitions and usage instructions.
.SH EXAMPLES
A complete example demonstrating how to write tests using the testing library can be found in the
.B crash_test_dummy.tgz
archive located at:
.RS
.I /usr/share/doc/termobulator/examples/crash_test_dummy.tgz
.RE
.PP
Extract this archive and view the included
.I CMakeLists.txt
and
.I crash_test_dummy_test.cc
for a working out-of-the-box configuration template.
